---
import Terminal from './Terminal.astro';

const differentiators = [
  {
    title: 'We built the platform',
    body: 'Six core components, shaped through real delivery work and available as open source before we ever step into your environment.',
  },
  {
    title: 'We embed, not advise',
    body: 'Our engineers work in your repositories, your CI, and your infrastructure. We author production code and integration docs with your team, not decks for a steering committee.',
  },
  {
    title: 'We transfer the keys',
    body: 'We structure the work for capability transfer from day one. Our footprint should shrink as your team takes over, and by the final phase we should be advisory, not essential.',
  },
];

const phases = [
  {
    name: 'Phase 1 - Foundation',
    meta: '2 weeks · fixed scope',
    body: 'We start on-site or remote by assessing your environment against the Visdom Maturity Matrix: 60 practices across four perspectives. We return a prioritized roadmap, name the first pilot team, identify the components that matter, and define the Phase 2 scope. If you stop there, your team still keeps the roadmap.',
    accent: 'var(--color-blue)',
  },
  {
    name: 'Phase 2 - Pilot Implementation',
    meta: '6-10 weeks · scoped after Phase 1',
    body: 'We deploy the recommended components with one pilot team inside your environment. We integrate with your source control, CI, identity, and observability stack. Our engineers and your platform team co-author the runbooks, ADRs, and integration docs, and your engineers co-own the code from the first week.',
    accent: 'var(--color-emerald)',
  },
  {
    name: 'Phase 3 - Scale and Transfer',
    meta: '4-8 weeks · advisory',
    body: 'Your platform team leads rollout across the wider organization. We stay close enough to unblock hard decisions, review architecture, and help with exceptions, but we are no longer driving day-to-day delivery. By the end, your team should be able to operate the platform without us.',
    accent: 'var(--color-purple)',
  },
  {
    name: 'Phase 4 - Ongoing partnership',
    meta: 'optional · retainer or on-call',
    body: 'After transfer you own the platform end-to-end. If you want a safety net, we offer a named-engineer retainer for architectural reviews, critical fixes on open-source components, and help with the next maturity step. No lock-in, no minimums - you call us when you need us, not the other way around.',
    accent: 'var(--color-amber)',
  },
];

---
<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <div id="different" class="fade-up">
      <p class="section-label">Operating model</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">We built the platform. We deliver the work. You keep the capability.</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle mb-14">
        We are not a software vendor selling licenses. We are not a traditional consultancy starting from zero in every client environment. We bring a six-component platform that we have deployed repeatedly, then we embed with your platform engineers to adapt it to your stack, your controls, and your delivery model. When the engagement ends, your team owns the capability and the codebase.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-24">
      {differentiators.map((item) => (
        <article class="card p-8 fade-up">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text mb-4">{item.title}</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div id="engage" class="fade-up mb-14">
      <p class="section-label">Engagement model</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">How we engage</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle mb-14">
        We structure engagements in three phases with capability transfer designed in from the start. You should end with the capability, not a dependency on us. A fourth phase is available as an optional retainer once the transfer is complete.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-10">
      {phases.map((phase) => (
        <article class="engagement-card fade-up" style={`--phase-accent: ${phase.accent}`}>
          <div class="engagement-head">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text">{phase.name}</h3>
            <span class="engagement-meta">{phase.meta}</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">{phase.body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="transfer-signal fade-up" aria-label="Capability transfer across engagement phases">
      <div class="transfer-step">
        <span class="transfer-step-label">Phase 1</span>
        <strong>VirtusLab leads</strong>
      </div>
      <div class="transfer-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="transfer-step">
        <span class="transfer-step-label">Phase 2</span>
        <strong>Deep collaboration</strong>
      </div>
      <div class="transfer-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="transfer-step">
        <span class="transfer-step-label">Phase 3</span>
        <strong>Your team leads</strong>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="kit" class="fade-up mt-24">
      <p class="section-label">Platform components</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">The platform we bring</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle mb-14">
        Every engagement uses some combination of these six components. Most teams still bring us in because composing them, hardening them, and integrating them into a real enterprise environment is the expensive part, and we have already done that work more than once.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
            <div class="fabric-diagram" aria-label="Visdom Context Fabric ingests repository, documentation, tickets, and CI data, then exposes deterministic answers to agents">
              <div class="fabric-column fabric-column--sources">
                <p class="fabric-column-label">Sources</p>
                {[
                  { name: 'Git repository', meta: 'code · history · blame' },
                  { name: 'Confluence / Notion', meta: 'ADRs · runbooks' },
                  { name: 'Jira / Linear', meta: 'tickets · ownership' },
                  { name: 'CI / Actions', meta: 'builds · artifacts' },
                  { name: 'CLAUDE.md / rules', meta: 'conventions' },
                ].map((item) => (
                  <div class="fabric-node">
                    <strong>{item.name}</strong>
                    <span>{item.meta}</span>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>

              <svg class="fabric-wires fabric-wires--in" viewBox="0 0 80 320" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M0,32 C40,32 40,160 80,160" />
                <path d="M0,96 C40,96 40,160 80,160" />
                <path d="M0,160 L80,160" />
                <path d="M0,224 C40,224 40,160 80,160" />
                <path d="M0,288 C40,288 40,160 80,160" />
              </svg>

              <div class="fabric-core">
                <span class="fabric-core-tag">VISDOM</span>
                <strong>Context Fabric</strong>
                <p>Ingest · normalize · index the repo's ground truth.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Ownership graph</li>
                  <li>Dependency &amp; blast radius</li>
                  <li>Convention index</li>
                  <li>Expertise ranking</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <svg class="fabric-wires fabric-wires--out" viewBox="0 0 80 320" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M0,160 C40,160 40,80 80,80" />
                <path d="M0,160 L80,160" />
                <path d="M0,160 C40,160 40,240 80,240" />
              </svg>

              <div class="fabric-column fabric-column--outputs">
                <p class="fabric-column-label">Deterministic answers</p>
                {[
                  { name: 'Who owns this?', meta: '@jkowalski · 0.87' },
                  { name: 'What breaks if I change it?', meta: 'blast radius: 12 files' },
                  { name: 'Where does this pattern exist?', meta: '3 precedents · src/auth/*' },
                ].map((item) => (
                  <div class="fabric-node fabric-node--output">
                    <strong>{item.name}</strong>
                    <span>{item.meta}</span>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
            <div class="component-number">01</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">Visdom Context Fabric</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Your agents hallucinate because your repo is a black box to them. Give agents, and every reviewer, deterministic answers to "who owns this, what breaks if I change it, where does this pattern already exist." Review rework drops. Refactors stop turning into incident retros.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              Powered by <span class="font-semibold text-text">Visdom Developer Intelligence</span>, deterministic code expertise, blast radius analysis, and ownership graphs via MCP.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">Open Source</span>
              <span class="tag bg-emerald/10 text-emerald border border-emerald/20">MCP Server</span>
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">CLI</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <a href="https://github.com/VirtusLab/visdom-developer-intelligence" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-primary text-sm">View on GitHub</a>
              <a href="https://github.com/VirtusLab/visdom-developer-intelligence" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Documentation</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <div class="component-number">02</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">
              Visdom Code Review
              <span class="text-base font-normal text-text-muted">VCR</span>
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Your seniors spend 30-50% of their week reviewing PRs they did not write. VCR reviews every PR with architectural context, catching boundary violations, security holes, and performance regressions before they hit production, so seniors only open the ones that actually need them. ~$0.10 per PR, no SaaS, runs in your CI.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Architecture</span>
              <span class="tag bg-amber/10 text-amber border border-amber/20">Security</span>
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">Performance</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <a href="https://virtuslab.github.io/visdom-code-review/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-primary text-sm">Read the Reference</a>
              <a href="https://virtuslab.github.io/visdom-code-review/before-after/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Before / After</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <figure class="screenshot-frame">
              <div class="screenshot-chrome" aria-hidden="true">
                <span></span><span></span><span></span>
                <span class="screenshot-title">vcr · review dashboard</span>
              </div>
              <img
                src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/vcr-dashboard.png`}
                alt="VCR dashboard showing findings per week across repositories, with critical findings, PR coverage and week-over-week trends"
                loading="lazy"
                width="1920"
                height="1080"
              />
              <figcaption>Findings, critical count, and PR coverage across repos — updated every CI run.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <div class="component-number">03</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">Visdom Testing</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              When AI writes both the code and the tests, line coverage stops meaning anything. Architecture gates, property-based, and mutation testing catch the computation bugs hiding behind 90% green CI, and the architectural drift your team already voted against.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              Powered by <span class="font-semibold text-text">Visdom Testing</span>, adaptive test shape tuned to your architecture, with ArchUnit gates that stop AI from drifting.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">ArchUnit</span>
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Property-Based</span>
              <span class="tag bg-amber/10 text-amber border border-amber/20">Mutation Testing</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <a href="https://virtuslab.github.io/visdom-testing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-primary text-sm">Read the Reference</a>
              <a href="https://virtuslab.github.io/visdom-testing/before-after/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Before / After</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <Terminal title="visdom-testing">
{`$ visdom test --strategy diamond
Layer 0: Architecture (ArchUnit)
  ├─ Layer boundaries          0/10 violations ✓
  ├─ Field injection           0/10 ✓
  └─ Forbidden APIs            0/10 ✓

Layer 1: Property-based (jqwik)
  ├─ 12 properties, 10k cases each
  └─ Rounding bug found in VAT.apply()

Layer 2: Mutation (PIT)
  ├─ Mutation score            73%
  └─ 2/2 computation bugs caught

`}<span class="text-emerald">Tests trusted ✓</span>
            </Terminal>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
            <div class="card accent-card p-8">
              <div class="space-y-5">
                {[
                  { label: 'Trace', desc: 'Session traces, token usage, tool calls, secret redaction', color: 'var(--color-emerald)' },
                  { label: 'Enforce', desc: 'Model allowlists, path protection, token budgets', color: 'var(--color-blue)' },
                  { label: 'Audit', desc: 'Ed25519 signatures, hash-chained records, SOX/PCI-DSS', color: 'var(--color-purple)' },
                  { label: 'Evaluate', desc: 'Auto-evaluation, model distribution, adoption patterns', color: 'var(--color-amber)' },
                  { label: 'Attribute', desc: 'Line-by-line AI code attribution via tree-sitter', color: 'var(--color-emerald)' },
                ].map(item => (
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3 group">
                    <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-hover:scale-150" style={`background: ${item.color}`}></span>
                    <div>
                      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-text">{item.label}</span>
                      <span class="text-xs text-text-muted ml-2">{item.desc}</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
            <div class="component-number">04</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">Visdom Governance</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Ship AI-generated code without the compliance bottleneck. A tamper-evident record of every agent interaction turns EU AI Act, SOX, and PCI-DSS requirements from a release blocker into a signed receipt, and gives legal the audit trail they need to say yes.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              Powered by <span class="font-semibold text-text">TraceVault</span>, a flight recorder for AI development with Ed25519-signed, hash-chained records and line-by-line AI attribution.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-emerald/10 text-emerald border border-emerald/20">Tracing</span>
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Audit Trail</span>
              <span class="tag bg-amber/10 text-amber border border-amber/20">EU AI Act</span>
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">Auto-Evaluation</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <a href="https://virtuslab.com/services/visdom" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-primary text-sm">Visdom Governance -&gt;</a>
              <a href="https://github.com/softwaremill/tracevault" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">GitHub</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <div class="component-number">05</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">Visdom Security</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Let agents move fast without betting the company on it. A rogue prompt cannot exfiltrate secrets, corrupt a database, or push to prod, because it never had the keys to begin with. Experimentation without the breach headline.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              Powered by <span class="font-semibold text-text">Sandcat</span>, ephemeral, fully isolated sandboxes with scoped credentials, egress allowlists, and policy guardrails built for agentic workflows.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-emerald/10 text-emerald border border-emerald/20">Isolation</span>
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">Policy Guardrails</span>
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Zero Blast Radius</span>
            </div>
            <a href="#contact" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Learn More -&gt;</a>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="sandbox-diagram" aria-label="Sandcat isolates the agent in an ephemeral sandbox, with an egress wall separating it from production">
              <div class="sandbox-zone sandbox-zone--inside">
                <p class="sandbox-zone-label">Sandcat · ephemeral sandbox</p>
                <div class="sandbox-agent">
                  <span class="sandbox-agent-tag">AGENT</span>
                  <div class="sandbox-agent-body">
                    <strong>sb-a1b2c3</strong>
                    <span>execute · test · iterate</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <ul class="sandbox-props">
                  <li><span>Scoped token</span><em>2h · read-only</em></li>
                  <li><span>Repo clone</span><em>from main</em></li>
                  <li><span>Policy</span><em>strict</em></li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="sandbox-wall" aria-hidden="true">
                <span class="sandbox-wall-label">EGRESS WALL</span>
                <ul class="sandbox-wall-list sandbox-wall-list--allow">
                  <li><span class="sandbox-mark sandbox-mark--ok">✓</span>npm / PyPI</li>
                  <li><span class="sandbox-mark sandbox-mark--ok">✓</span>LLM APIs</li>
                  <li><span class="sandbox-mark sandbox-mark--ok">✓</span>test services</li>
                </ul>
                <ul class="sandbox-wall-list sandbox-wall-list--deny">
                  <li><span class="sandbox-mark sandbox-mark--no">✗</span>prod database</li>
                  <li><span class="sandbox-mark sandbox-mark--no">✗</span>secrets vault</li>
                  <li><span class="sandbox-mark sandbox-mark--no">✗</span>deploy pipeline</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="sandbox-zone sandbox-zone--outside">
                <p class="sandbox-zone-label">Production</p>
                <div class="sandbox-prod">
                  <span class="sandbox-prod-lock" aria-hidden="true">
                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                      <rect x="4" y="10" width="16" height="11" rx="2" />
                      <path d="M8 10 V7 a4 4 0 1 1 8 0 v3" />
                    </svg>
                  </span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Unreachable by design</strong>
                    <span>No credentials. No path. No blast radius.</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
            <div class="card accent-card p-8">
              <div class="space-y-6">
                {[
                  { label: 'Build time reduction', value: '-88%', width: '88%', note: 'Global logistics, Scala monorepo, sbt -> Bazel. 40-60 min -> 5 min.' },
                  { label: 'PR merge time', value: '-43%', width: '43%', note: 'Investment bank, Scala monorepo, managed IntelliJ IDEA.' },
                  { label: 'Agent iteration speed', value: '50x/hr', width: '95%', note: 'Target cadence for coding agents - the speed today\'s pipelines need to keep up with.' },
                ].map(item => (
                  <div>
                    <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-2">
                      <span class="text-text-secondary">{item.label}</span>
                      <span class="font-semibold text-emerald">{item.value}</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="h-2.5 bg-surface-light rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                      <div class="h-full rounded-full progress-bar" style={`width: ${item.width}; background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--color-emerald), var(--color-blue))`}></div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="metric-note">{item.note}</p>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
              <p class="metric-footnote">
                Client names under NDA. Full write-ups on the
                <a href="https://virtuslab.com/success-stories/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">VirtusLab success stories</a>
                page.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
            <div class="component-number">06</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
              Visdom Machine CI
              <span class="tag bg-amber/10 text-amber border border-amber/20 text-xs font-medium normal-case tracking-normal">Coming Soon</span>
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Your CI takes 45 minutes. An AI agent iterates 50x per hour. The mismatch burns tokens on agents looping against a pipeline built for humans. We re-architect yours to run at machine speed, the same 88% build-time reduction we have delivered on production JVM fleets.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-text-muted mb-3">Built on</p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <a href="https://bazel.build/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="logo-chip" aria-label="Bazel">
                <img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/bazel-logo.svg`} alt="" width="22" height="22" />
                <span>Bazel</span>
              </a>
              <a href="https://www.engflow.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="logo-chip logo-chip--wordmark" aria-label="EngFlow">
                <img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/engflow-logo.png`} alt="EngFlow" height="22" />
              </a>
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Gradle</span>
              <span class="tag bg-amber/10 text-amber border border-amber/20">Performance</span>
            </div>
            <a href="https://virtuslab.com/blog/ai/the-fallacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Read: "The Ferrari Engine in a Fiat 500" -&gt;</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .engagement-card {
    position: relative;
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px 0 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.05);
  }

  .engagement-card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 4px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl) 0 0 var(--radius-xl);
    background: var(--phase-accent);
  }

  .engagement-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .engagement-meta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.45rem 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .footprint-line {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .metric-note {
    margin-top: 0.45rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .metric-footnote {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
